column5: ok, not looking for a good restaurant in Int. Falls, but in Fort Frances. We like to cross the border and get settled into our motel (Super 8) before having supper. We've eaten at Kettles several times but are looking for other suggestions this year. Thanks!
Try Le Rendevous, east side of town. If you want fast and good, try Tim Horton's.
The Chocolate Moose is the best. Great breakfast also! Been going for years!
Was sorry to see the Firehouse change hands. That place was great.
We are looking for a place to get a walleye dinner in Int. Falls. Nothing fancy, just good food. Thanks in advance.
ditto the moose, on Hwy 53 by the Days Inn & Super 8.

We dine a few times a year at the ol la chocolate' Moouse. me and the boys dig it, has good walleye dinner on the menu, the the kids dig it cause a moose made of chocolate is a cool thing. not too fancy, most times we come through there, we are pretty road gruby smelling like fish and other choice things. that is not the only place in the area but certainly the best i have found over the years.
Another Ditto on the Moose. Great milk shakes to.
Shorelunch Cafe. Mom and Pop diner. Good food, fast service.
Barney's , across the parking lot from the grocery store
for our last good restaurant meal bdfore leaving the states for a week we would eat at the holiday inn west of town
Chocolate Moose by all means. You can't go wrong there.
